    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-07-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="30"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d30">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Denby</persName>, chargé, to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 31.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-07-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 27, 1894</hi>
                        </date>. (Received September 11.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that the Emperor has
                    nominated two commissioners to investigate and report upon the Viceroy Li’s
                    conduct of the Korean business. These commissioners are Weng Tung-ho, president
                    of the board of revenue, and Li Hung-tsao, president of the board of rites.</p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Chas. Denby</hi>, Jr.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
